<TEXT>
a quickspreading outbreak of chinese flu has ruined 
the holidays for tens of thousands of italians filled hospitals and 
clinics and left many doctors sick in bed italian newspapers 
report 
the outbreak surprised health officials who had predicted the 
annual flu season would begin in january according to news reports 
wednesday 
while health officials do not consider this years virus which 
they think originated in chinese pigs to be more severe than recent 
types its timing has caused numerous problems 
throughout italy family doctors understaffed emergency rooms 
and clinics were unprepared for the onslaught of people seeking 
relief from the virus which is considered dangerous only to infants 
and the elderly there have been no reports of deaths in italy from 
the flu 
in rome weekend calls to the citys main emergency center poured 
in at almost twice the normal rate an estimated 15 percent of the 
citys doctors and 35 percent of its nurses were unable to work 
mostly due to the virus 
health officials in bologna estimate that about 20000 citizens 
remain in bed with symptoms of the flu which include high fever 
aching joints and the chills 
doctors have said the flu normally lasts three days and should be 
treated with rest fluids aspirin and vitamin c 
</TEXT>
