<TEXT>
the picasso museum home for the past three years to 
nearly 3500 works by pablo picasso is closing to the public for 
two months for repairs a museum spokesman said 
the refurbished 17th century mansion known as the hotel sale 
after one of its former owners opened as a museum in 1985 with the 
worlds largest collection of works by the spanish master who died 
in 1973 
the 203 paintings 158 sculptures and 3000 drawings were taken 
by the french government from picassos heirs in lieu of death 
taxes along with works by matisse cezanne braque and renoir in 
the artists private collection 
a spokesman said wednesday that the repairs involved replacing 
the buildings stone floors which had proven too porous and 
fragile to handle traffic from some 40000 visitors monthly 
the museum closes saturday and reopens march 1 
</TEXT>
