a dozen environmentalists protesting 
east bloc air pollution erected two tents on the east german side of 
the border as communist border guards watched without intervening 
west german police said 
police said the activists staged the protest wednesday just 
inside east germany near where west germany east germany and 
czechoslovakia meet 
the environmentalists contend east german and czechoslovak 
authorities are too lax in enforcing air pollution laws resulting 
in harmful emissions that affect air quality in west germany as well 
twelve of them erected two tents just inside the east german 
frontier but outside the fence that separates the two countries 
they also released balloons with slogans such as pollution knows 
no borders 
west german police said east german border guards watched the 
developments from a distance but did not intervene czechoslovak 
sentries also watched from their side of the border 
five other environmentalists stayed on west german territory as 
the protest continued late wednesday 
