<TEXT>
president reagans decision to extend us 
territorial waters an additional nine miles offshore will make it 
more difficult for foreign countries to spy on american shores 
administration officials say 
reagan took the action wednesday at the bel air home where he 
will live after jan 20 he and first lady nancy reagan are spending 
the holidays there but were leaving today for three days in palm 
springs 
by a proclamation the president extended us sovereignty and 
jurisdiction from the present three miles to 12 miles 
maureen walker a foreign affairs officer in the state 
departments office of ocean law and policy said the extension 
makes the united states the 105th country to claim a 12mile limit 
the 12mile limit was called for in 1982 by the united nations 
convention on the law of the sea and the us action leaves only 
six countries claiming narrower bands of offshore water finland and 
norway claim four miles each and the dominican republic greece 
israel and turkey each claim six miles ms walker said 
it will make foreign intelligencegathering more difficult and 
less effective because foreign ships will no longer be able to 
station themselves off our shores within the 12mile limit the 
state department officer said 
the proclamation assures foreign ships the right of innocent 
passage through us territorial waters and the right to pass 
through straits 
ms walker said it would not affect us and state laws that 
govern offshore mineral and fishing rights 
it applies to the waters off the united states puerto rico 
guam american samoa the us virgin islands the northern mariana 
islands and any other territory over which the united states 
exercises sovereignty it applies to airspace over the ocean as 
well as the waters and the bed and subsoil of the ocean 
in another action the president extended for six months the 
state of emergency that he proclaimed in 1986 between the united 
states and libya the step was needed to continue in effect the 
presidents 1986 order blocking libyan assets in the united states 
in retaliation for alleged terrorist action 
the president also signed a sevenpage executive order 
implementing the 1100page trade act passed by the last congress 
white house deputy press secretary leslye arsht said the order will 
enable the united states to continue effectively to work for more 
open world markets and strengthened international institutions 
ms arsht said the presidents national security adviser lt 
gen colin l powell telephoned him at the bel air home to inform 
him of the announcement by the british department of transport that 
last weeks crash of pan american flight 103 in scotland was caused 
by a bomb 
the investigation will continue to determine how the explosives 
were introduced into the plane she said the fbi and the faa 
are working closely with the british and scottish authorities on the 
investigation we are determined to find out who did it using all 
available resources 
