a flight carrying 40 passengers was diverted for an 
unscheduled landing at logan international airport wednesday after 
losing cabin pressurization apparently due to a faulty valve 
officials said 
continental airlines flight 269 from hartford conn to 
cleveland had been airborne for about a half hour when the cabin of 
the boeing 737 aircraft depressurized said continental spokesman 
dave messing in houston passengers were told to use oxygen masks 
and noone was injured he said 
the flight was diverted to logan where it landed without 
incident at about 5 pm and passengers were put on other flights 
the plane was to be repaired overnight messing said 
the mechanics are looking at it at this point it appears the 
depressurization stemmed from a faulty valve in the pressurization 
system he said 
