<TEXT>
prime minister benazir bhutto had her 
first meeting with prime minister rajiv gandhi of india on thursday 
and urged her fellow south asian leaders to spend less money on 
weapons and more on fighting disease and poverty 
ms bhutto assumed the chairmanship of the south asian 
association for regional cooperation and opened the first session of 
the sevennation summit then met with the leader of the nation that 
has long been her countrys bitter rival 
less than a month after pakistans first free elections in 11 
years propelled her into the prime ministers job and made her the 
first woman leader of a modern moslem nation ms bhutto used the 
summit to call for a reassessment of priorities in the impoverished 
asian subcontinent 
some of us are spending too great a proportion of our national 
resources on defense maintaining large military forces that face 
each other ms bhutto said speaking in english with an accent 
that reflects both her harvard and oxford educations 
ms bhutto whose country spends almost 40 percent of its budget 
on defense added the truth is that our people face the same 
common problems the problems of poverty disease slums ignorance 
and unemployment and it is to the vanquishing of these enemies 
that we should direct all our efforts 
gandhi in his speech at the opening session in the auditorium of 
the state bank building also spoke of the need to translate the 
groups scores of seminars and study groups into concrete action 
in each of our countries the highest priority is the war on 
poverty gandhi said until we make the south asian association 
for regional cooperation a peoples movement its achievements will 
lie recorded only in dusty files or molder in the cabinets of our 
bureaucracies 
we have not taken even one full step down the road towards 
regional cooperation of a kind which interfaces with our people on 
development issues at the grassroots ghe said 
ms bhutto urged fellow members to seek regional solutions for 
curbing the arms race and the danger of nuclear proliferation of 
war 
indias nuclear weapons program and pakistans ability to 
manufacture nuclear arms have been a major obstacle to friendlier 
relations between the two countries 
moslem pakistan has fought three wars with predominantly hindu 
india since 1947 when the two nations were created through 
partition along religious lines out of the british colonial india 
ms bhutto chatted occasionally with gandhi while seated on the 
platform at the 2hour opening session of the fourth annual summit 
she saw him privately afterward and two more private sessions are 
scheduled friday and saturday 
their meeting has eclipsed the presence of the five other 
leaders president hussain muhammad ershad of bangladesh king jigme 
singhe wangchuk of bhutan president maumoon abdul gayoom of the 
maldives king birendra of nepal and president junius r jayewardene 
of sri lanka 
but the summit by providing a venue for gandhi and ms bhutto to 
get to know each other has prompted hopes that this new generation 
of indian and pakistani leaders can transcend the bitter memories of 
their nations intertwined histories 
gandhi 44 took office in 1984 after the assassination of his 
mother prime minister indira gandhi ms bhutto 35 led her 
pakistan peoples party to an electoral triumph in last months 
parliament elections on dec 2 she was sworn in as prime minister 
a post held by her father prime minister zulkifar ali bhutto who 
was ousted in a military coup in 1977 and later executed 
india with 880 million people and pakistan with 107 million 
are the mightiest military and political powers of the nations 
which have a combined population of 11 billion 
</TEXT>
