predominantly mixedrace western cape students congress one of a 
dozen youth and student groups banned this year 
thousands of mixedrace students around cape town in some cases 
supported by faculty staged a widespread classroom boycott in april 
to protest detentions and harassment of students and teachers 
the latest bannings were denounced by south africas human rights 
commission it described the government as powerdrunk and said 
that only 24 organizations had been banned in a 37year period 
before 1988 
the newly banned organizations have never been accused in court 
of any illegal actions the commission said in a statement 
