presidentelect bush expressing horror 
that a us jetliner was downed by a bomb said thursday he would 
seek hard and punish firmly those responsible if they can be 
found 
but bush said it would be imprudent for him or any other 
official to discuss what kind of action can be taken to 
retaliate against terrorists 
bush who has been secluded at a 10000acre south texas ranch 
hunting quail for three days said he had no other information than 
what was in the public domain about the bomb that blew up a pan 
american jetliner over scotland last week the crash killed 259 
passengers and crew members and 11 people on the ground 
the vice president made his comments as he left chase naval air 
station in beeville texas headed for pintala about 15 miles from 
montgomery 
