or wounded 7932 soldiers this year and a human rights group said 
1747 civilians died in that time in el salvadors civil war 
a report on the rebels radio venceremos gave no breakdown of 
dead and wounded nor did it say how many guerrillas were killed 
it claimed the guerrillas from the farabundo marti national 
liberation front caused 3 million in property damage through 
sabotage attacks including those on numerous military installations 
the independent human rights commission of el salvador said 1747 
civilians were killed in violent conflicts this year and 231 
civilians were reported missing 
commission spokesman celia medrano told a news conference the 
numbers were up from last year when the group reported 1415 
civilians killed and 204 missing 
the head of the militarys joint chiefs of staff col rene 
emilio ponce recently said the army killed 914 guerrillas and 
wounded 702 in 1988 
like the rebels the military did not mention its own casualties 
however the military said it suffered a combined total of 2039 
deaths and injuries between june 1987 and may 1988 
president jose napoleon duarte condemned violence from both the 
left and right late wednesday after returning from washington where 
he underwent an evaluation of chemotherapy he is receiving for 
terminal liver cancer 
his successor to be chosen in presidential elections in march 
must seek an end to the 9year conflict he said 
if not we are going to bring the country to a moment of 
gigantic confrontations duarte said we must seek the path of 
tolerance and comprehension 
about 65500 people mostly civilians have been killed in the 
war between rebels and usbacked governments since 1979 
