suggestion all the blame for the economic 
illiteracy so widespread in the american populace should not fall 
on the nations schools 
it is not just in the classroom that economics is shrouded in 
ignorance mystery and superstitution but also in politics and 
government in the workplace and in the shopping mall and just 
about everywhere else you care to look 
for example when congressmen discuss the state of the economy 
with officials of the federal reserve board emotion and political 
prejudices often overshadow the whole debate 
legislators are wont to charge that the fed is heedlessly hurting 
their constituents by setting interest rates too high 
a fed official counters by declaring that the fed doesnt set 
interest rates market forces do and interest rates would be a lot 
lower if only congress stopped voting for inflationary spending 
programs and balanced its budget for a change 
ordinary citizens may not have been given much schooling on the 
factors that determine interest rates or on the workings of the fed 
but they may quickly come to the conclusion that both sides in 
this argument are engaged in some selfserving posturing 
the results of an economics test given to more than 8000 high 
school students made a lot of headlines when they were made public 
the other day 
fewer than half of the students it was reported showed a grasp 
of such basic economic concepts as inflation and the gross national 
product our schools are producing a nation of economic 
illiterates said one of the studys authors 
some of the sample questions from the test were not as simple as 
they looked though if you consider the emotional baggage that 
comes with so many basic economic terms 
one multiplechoice item for instance called for a definition 
of profits by the time they reach high school how many 
americans have not heard that word used as a pejorative 
would the question have read the same if the testtakers were 
asked to define earnings of a business or net income 
if economic ignorance begins in the schools a case can certainly 
be made that it is perpetuated by the pillars of capitalism as it is 
practiced in this country 
the bank that gives away free toaster ovens to new depositors 
