the stock market advanced broadly today sending 
its bestknown index above its highest closing level of the year in 
a rally that analysts attributed to yearend bargain hunting 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials which rose 375 points 
on wednesday was up 1750 at 218393 with two hours left in the 
session 
the dow jones industrial averages highest close this year was 
218350 reached on oct 21 
advancing issues outpaced losers by a margin of 2 to 1 among 
issues listed on the new york stock exchange with 949 up 482 down 
and 513 unchanged 
volume on the big board came to 9392 million shares at 2 pm on 
wall street compared with 7938 million shares at the same point 
wednesday 
analysts said yearend bargain hunting was putting some upward 
pressure on prices they said the gains reflects efforts by some 
institutional investors to spruce up their endofyear portfolios by 
adding some topquality issues 
with the market near its highs for the year the large cash 
position that some money managers find themselves with is 
embarrassing said newton d zinder senior vice president at 
shearson lehman hutton inc 
he said the gains today also reflected some confidence in the 
stock market to hold its ground despite rising interest rates 
earlier in the week 
yields on some shortterm treasury issues for instance have 
risen above 9 percent and pose competition for the uncertain returns 
on stocks 
