<TEXT>
american public radio will introduce a 
new daily halfhour business program on tuesday with a variety of 
politicians and economists set to serve as contributors 
marketplace hosted by former wall street journal reporter 
michael creedman will be heard on more than 80 stations across the 
country 
scheduled guests include former presidential candidate bruce 
babbitt bestselling author tom peters commodities expert richard 
dennis venture capitalist kip hagopian us sen william proxmire 
and former congressman ed zschau 
the show produced in long beach will focus on both consumer and 
international business news 
</TEXT>
