<TEXT>
pennwalt escalated efforts thursday to 
prevent a hostile takeover by filing a federal lawsuit accusing 
centaur partners of violating securities laws in a recent tender 
offer 
the suit seeks an injunction against centaurs 765 million 
offer which was filed dec 13 with the securities and exchange 
commission 
a news statement released thursday night named painewebber as an 
undisclosed joint partner with centaur 
the statement said the lawsuit demands among other things that 
centaur and its affiliates correct the false and misleading 
statements in the tender offer materials 
the statement did not include details of pennwalts allegations 
a pennwalt spokeswoman sue s kinard said thursday night that she 
had not read the suit and could not comment 
she referred all questions to matt broderick of the 
philadelphiabased law firm dechart price and rhoads broderick 
did not return a telephone call from the associated press thursday 
night 
pennwalts board of directors on tuesday called centaurs 
100pershare offer completely unacceptable 
officials of centaur an investment partnership have said they 
will continue to press ahead with the takeover bid and want to meet 
with pennwalt executives to discuss a friendly merger pennwalt has 
said no meeting will occur 
in a letter to pennwalt shareholders chairman edwin r tuttle 
called centaurs offer illusory and said it was not intended to 
succeed 
centaur whose principals are new york financiers abbey j butler 
and melvyn j estrin owns 127 percent of the chemical makers 
outstanding shares 
pennwalt closed thursday at 103 on the new york stock exchange 
down 
</TEXT>
